'''Maxim Peter M. De Cuyper''' ({{IPA|nl|ˈmɑksɪm də ˈkœypər}}; born 22 December 2000) is a Belgian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Full-back (association football)|full-back]] or [[left midfielder]] for {{English football updater|Brigh&HA}} club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]].

==Club career==

===Club Brugge===
De Cuyper began his career at the youth academy of [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]]. On 20 February 2020, De Cuyper made his professional debut for Brugge against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in the first-leg of the [[UEFA Europa League]] Round of 32. He started and played 73 minutes as Club Brugge drew 1–1.<ref>{{cite web |title=Club Brugge 1–1 Manchester United |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/02/20/europe/uefa-cup/club-brugge-kv/manchester-united-fc/3194327/ |website=Soccerway}}</ref> De Cuyper was then a starter again for Brugge in the second leg of the tie and played the whole match as Brugge fell 0–5.<ref>{{cite web |title=Manchester United 5–0 Club Brugge |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/02/27/europe/uefa-cup/manchester-united-fc/club-brugge-kv/3194328/ |website=Soccerway}}</ref> On 30 August 2020, De Cuyper made his debut for [[Club Brugge KV#Reserves and Club NXT (Youth Academy)|Club NXT]], Brugge's reserve team, in [[Belgian First Division B]]. He came on as a 64th minute substitute as Brugge were defeated 2–2.<ref>{{cite web |title=Club NXT 2–2 Lommel |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/08/30/belgium/second-division/belgium-club-brugge-kv-ii/kvsk-united-overpelt-lommel/3323824/ |website=Soccerway}}</ref> On 4 February 2022, Club Brugge announced that they had extended de Cuyper's contract through 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/news/thomas-van-den-keybus-and-maxim-de-cuyper-sign-new-contract-until-2025|title=Thomas Van den Keybus and Maxim De Cuyper sign new contract until 2025|website=clubbrugge.be|date=4 February 2022|access-date=27 July 2022}}</ref>

====Westerlo (loan)====
On 2 August 2021, he joined [[K.V.C. Westerlo|Westerlo]] on loan for the 2021–22 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[K.V.C. Westerlo|Westerlo]]|url=https://kvcwesterlo.be/welcome-maxim-de-cuyper/|title=Welcome Maxime De Cuyper|date=2 August 2021|accessdate=18 October 2021|archive-date=3 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221103220203/https://kvcwesterlo.be/welcome-maxim-de-cuyper/|url-status=dead}}</ref> The loan was extended for the 2022–23 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Westerlo|url=https://kvcwesterlo.be/maxim-remains-kemphaan/|title=Maxim remains 'Kemphaan'|access-date=18 August 2022|archive-date=29 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220929183803/https://kvcwesterlo.be/maxim-remains-kemphaan/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Brighton & Hove Albion===
[[File:Maxim De Cuyper 24012026 (1).jpg|thumb|left|200px|De Cuyper with [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] in 2026.]]

On 5 July 2025, De Cuyper transferred to [[Premier League]] club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] for an undisclosed transfer fee, signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/media-article/mft-transfer-news-maxim-de-cuyper-club-brugge-july-2025|title=Albion sign Maxim De Cuyper from Club Brugge|publisher=Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|access-date=5 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Brighton sign defender De Cuyper from Club Brugge |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cvg6mx7zjz2o |access-date=5 July 2025 |publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |date=5 July 2025}}</ref> On 16 August, he made his debut for the club in a 1–1 draw against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] in the league.<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 August 2025 |title=Brighton 1–1 Fulham: Late Muniz equaliser earns visitors a draw |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/740598 |access-date=23 August 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
De Cuyper made his debut for the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]] on 5 June 2024 in a friendly against [[Montenegro national football team|Montenegro]]. He played the full game in a 2–0 victory at [[King Baudouin Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698284/|title=Belgium v Montenegro game report|date=5 June 2024}}</ref> De Cuyper was selected for the Belgium National team for the [[UEFA Euro 2024|2024 Euros]],<ref>{{Cite news |date=28 May 2024 |title=25 Devils go to EURO 2024 |url=https://www.rbfa.be/en/news/25-devils-go-euro-2024 |publisher=[[Royal Belgian Football Association]] |access-date=12 October 2024}}</ref> but was an unused substitute in all 4 of Belgium's games.
De Cuyper scored his first goal for Belgium in a 2–2 draw against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] on 10 October 2024.<ref>{{cite web |date=10 October 2024 |title=Italy-Belgium UEFA Nations League 2025 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/match/2040102/ |publisher=UEFA |access-date=12 October 2024}}</ref>

